coſ nos paragetas: 1. Ioh. 2.17. or as ſome render, the glittering ſhew thereof withdrawes and ſteales away the heart from God. How many haue our owne eyes ſeene, mirrours of holy carriage in their meane eſtate, whom the loue of aduancement, and the enioying thereof hath made ouer diſſolute? would God, not alſo ſcandalous to their profeſſion.
